nl: In which years did Meaghan Francella play more than 20 tournaments, how many times did she win in those years, and what was her average scoring average during those years?
sql:
SELECT `Year`, 
       SUM(CASE WHEN `Tournaments played` > 20 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `Number of Years Played More Than 20 Tournaments`,
       SUM(CASE WHEN `Wins` > 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `Number of Years With Wins`,
       AVG(`Scoring average`) AS `Average Scoring Average`
FROM `table_1_10021158_3`
GROUP BY `Year`
ORDER BY `Year`;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, 
       SUM(CASE WHEN col1 > 20 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `Number of Years Played More Than 20 Tournaments`,
       SUM(CASE WHEN col3 > 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS `Number of Years With Wins`,
       AVG(col9) AS `Average Scoring Average`
FROM `table_1_10021158_3`
GROUP BY col0
ORDER BY col0;

nl: For each year, provide the average typhus incidence, the maximum typhoid fever incidence, the minimum relapsing fever incidence, the total smallpox cases, and the malaria data
sql:
SELECT 
        `Year`, 
        AVG(`Typhus`) AS `Average Typhus Incidence`, 
        MAX(`Typhoid fever`) AS `Highest Typhoid Fever Incidence`, 
        MIN(`Relapsing fever`) AS `Lowest Relapsing Fever Incidence`, 
        SUM(`Smallpox`) AS `Total Smallpox Cases`, 
        `Malaria`
    FROM 
        `table_1_1007688_1`
    GROUP BY 
        `Year`
    ORDER BY 
        `Year`;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0, 
        AVG(col1) AS `Average Typhus Incidence`, 
        MAX(col2) AS `Highest Typhoid Fever Incidence`, 
        MIN(col3) AS `Lowest Relapsing Fever Incidence`, 
        SUM(col4) AS `Total Smallpox Cases`, 
        col5
    FROM 
        `table_1_1007688_1`
    GROUP BY 
        col0
    ORDER BY 
        col0;

    JOIN table_1_10120207_8 AS T2 ON T1.`Season` = T2.`Season` 
    GROUP BY T1.`Season`
    ORDER BY T1.`Season` DESC;
actual_sql:

           SUM(T2.col6), COUNT(T2.col6)

    JOIN table_1_10120207_8 AS T2 ON T1.col0 = T2.col0 
    GROUP BY T1.col0

nl: What metrics are calculated for each year in the NASCAR Nationwide Series, including the total number of starts, wins, top five finishes, top ten finishes, unique teams used, average starting position, average finishing position, highest winnings, and final position?
sql:
SELECT `Year`, `Starts`, `Wins`, SUM(`Top 5`) AS TopFive, SUM(`Top 10`) AS TopTen, COUNT(DISTINCT `Team(s)`) AS TeamsUsed, AVG(`Avg. Start`) AS AvgStart, AVG(`Avg. Finish`) AS AvgFinish, MAX(`Winnings`) AS HighestWinnings, `Position` 
    FROM `table_1_1012730_2` 
    GROUP BY `Year` 
    ORDER BY `Year` ASC;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, col1, col2, SUM(col3) AS TopFive, SUM(col4) AS TopTen, COUNT(DISTINCT col10) AS TeamsUsed, AVG(col6) AS AvgStart, AVG(col7) AS AvgFinish, MAX(col8) AS HighestWinnings, col9 
    FROM `table_1_1012730_2` 
    GROUP BY col0 
    ORDER BY col0 ASC;

nl: Which assembly types, adhesives, times, temperatures, and pressures meet the criteria of being flex-based or using acrylic adhesive?
sql:

        `Assembly Type`, 
        `Adhesive Type`, 
        `Time(Sec)`, 
        `Temp (°C)`, 
        `Pressure`
    FROM 
        table_1_10262329_1

        (`Assembly Type` LIKE '%Flex%' OR `Adhesive Type` LIKE '%Acryl%')

            WHEN `Assembly Type` LIKE '%Flex%' THEN 1
            ELSE 0
        END, 
        `Temp (°C)` DESC;

        col0, 
        col1, 
        col2, 
        col3, 
        col4
    FROM 
        table_1_10262329_1
    WHERE 
        (col0 LIKE '%Flex%' OR col1 LIKE '%Acryl%')
    ORDER BY 
        CASE 
            WHEN col0 LIKE '%Flex%' THEN 1
            ELSE 0
        END, 
        col3 DESC;

nl: In how many school years did the team consist of only one distinct name?
sql:
SELECT `School Year`, COUNT(*) AS TeamCount
    FROM (
        SELECT DISTINCT `School Year`, SUBSTR(`Class A`, 1, LENGTH(`Class A`) - 1) AS Team
        FROM `table_1_10399701_2`
    )
    GROUP BY `School Year`
    ORDER BY `School Year`;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, COUNT(*) AS TeamCount
    FROM (
        SELECT DISTINCT col0, SUBSTR(col1, 1, LENGTH(col1) - 1) AS Team
        FROM `table_1_10399701_2`
    )
    GROUP BY col0
    ORDER BY col0;

nl: Which teams had the highest average wins, most points, and lowest position across the specified seasons?
sql:
SELECT `Team`, AVG(`Wins`) AS Avg_Wins, MAX(`Points`) AS Max_Points, MIN(`Position`) AS Min_Position
FROM `table_1_10420426_1`
WHERE `Season` BETWEEN '2005' AND '2011'
GROUP BY `Team`
ORDER BY `Max_Points` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT col2, AVG(col4) AS Avg_Wins, MAX(col8) AS Max_Points, MIN(col9) AS Min_Position
FROM `table_1_10420426_1`
WHERE col0 BETWEEN '2005' AND '2011'
GROUP BY col2

nl: How many regular season championships and playoff appearances did each team have per year?
sql:

    GROUP BY `Year`, `Division`, `League`
    ORDER BY `Year` DESC;

    GROUP BY col0, col1, col2

nl: ```What are the titles, directors, writers, and count of US air dates for episodes released in June or July?```
sql:
SELECT T1.`Title`, T1.`Director`, T1.`Writer`, COUNT(*) AS `Number of Air Dates`
    FROM `table_1_10470082_3` AS T1
    INNER JOIN (
        SELECT `Title`, GROUP_CONCAT(`US air date`, ', ') AS `US air dates`
        FROM `table_1_10470082_3`
        GROUP BY `Title`
    ) AS T2
    ON T1.`Title` = T2.`Title`
    WHERE T1.`US air date` LIKE '%June%' OR T1.`US air date` LIKE '%July%'
    GROUP BY T1.`Title`, T1.`Director`, T1.`Writer`
    ORDER BY `Number of Air Dates` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT T1.col2, T1.col3, T1.col4, COUNT(*) AS `Number of Air Dates`
    FROM `table_1_10470082_3` AS T1
    INNER JOIN (
        SELECT col2, GROUP_CONCAT(col5, ', ') AS `US air dates`
        FROM `table_1_10470082_3`
        GROUP BY col2
    ) AS T2
    ON T1.col2 = T2.col2
    WHERE T1.col5 LIKE '%June%' OR T1.col5 LIKE '%July%'
    GROUP BY T1.col2, T1.col3, T1.col4
    ORDER BY `Number of Air Dates` DESC;

nl: How many seasons have been won in each region or country listed?
sql:
SELECT `Region/country`, COUNT(*) AS `Number of Seasons`
    FROM (
        SELECT `Region/country`, `Seasons` 
        FROM (
            SELECT `Region/country`, `Winners` AS `Seasons`
            FROM `table_1_1053802_1`
            WHERE `Winners` LIKE '%Season%'
        )
    )
    GROUP BY `Region/country`
    ORDER BY `Number of Seasons` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, COUNT(*) AS `Number of Seasons`
    FROM (
        SELECT col0, `Seasons` 
        FROM (
            SELECT col0, col3 AS `Seasons`
            FROM `table_1_1053802_1`
            WHERE col3 LIKE '%Season%'
        )
    )
    GROUP BY col0
    ORDER BY `Number of Seasons` DESC;

nl: ```What seasons did Swindon Town play more than 15 league games and over 1 cup game?```
sql:
SELECT `Season`, `Team`, SUM(`League Apps`) AS TotalLeagueApps, SUM(`Cup Apps`) AS TotalCupApps 
    FROM table_1_10556257_1 
    GROUP BY `Season`, `Team` 
    HAVING TotalLeagueApps > 15 AND TotalCupApps > 1;
actual_sql:

    FROM table_1_10556257_1 
    GROUP BY col0, col1 
    HAVING TotalLeagueApps > 15 AND TotalCupApps > 1;

sql:

FROM table_1_10621256_1 
WHERE `100` > 0 
GROUP BY `Player` 
ORDER BY Average_After_Ten DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, SUM(col1) AS Total_Matches, AVG(col6) AS Average_After_Ten, MAX(col7) AS Highest_Score_Before_Fifty 
FROM table_1_10621256_1 
WHERE col7 > 0 
GROUP BY col0 
ORDER BY Average_After_Ten DESC;

nl: What are the average population per capita, the highest production, the lowest export, the total CO2 emissions, and the total emissions for each electricity level, sorted by total emissions in descending order?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Electricity`, 
        AVG(`Capita`) AS Average_Capita,
        MAX(`Production`) AS Highest_Production,
        MIN(`Export`) AS Lowest_Export,
        SUM(`CO 2 -emission`) AS Total_Emissions
    FROM 
        `table_1_10921309_1`
    GROUP BY 
        `Electricity`
    ORDER BY 
        `Total_Emissions` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col5, 
        AVG(col1) AS Average_Capita,
        MAX(col3) AS Highest_Production,
        MIN(col4) AS Lowest_Export,
        SUM(col6) AS Total_Emissions
    FROM 
        `table_1_10921309_1`
    GROUP BY 
        col5
    ORDER BY 
        `Total_Emissions` DESC;

sql:
SELECT `English title`, `Premiere`, `Finale`
FROM (
    SELECT `English title`, `Premiere`, `Finale`, 
           COUNT(*) OVER () AS total_series, 
           AVG(`Average`) AS avg_viewership, 
           RANK() OVER (ORDER BY AVG(`Average`) DESC) AS rank
    FROM `table_1_10942714_1`
) subquery
WHERE rank = 1 AND `Premiere` < `Finale`
ORDER BY `Premiere` ASC;
actual_sql:

FROM (
    SELECT col1, col5, col6, 
           COUNT(*) OVER () AS total_series, 
           AVG(col3) AS avg_viewership, 
           RANK() OVER (ORDER BY AVG(col3) DESC) AS rank
    FROM `table_1_10942714_1`
) subquery
WHERE rank = 1 AND col5 < col6
ORDER BY col5 ASC;

nl: What is the pick number, team, player name, position, and college for the first pick of each CFL team?
sql:
SELECT `Pick #`, `CFL Team`, `Player`, `Position`, `College`
    FROM (
        SELECT *,
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY `Pick #`) AS rn
        FROM (
            SELECT `Pick #`, `CFL Team`, `Player`, `Position`, `College`
            FROM `table_1_10975034_4`
        ) t
    )
    WHERE rn IN (
        SELECT rn
        FROM (
            SELECT *,
                   ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY `CFL Team` ORDER BY `Pick #`)
            FROM (
                SELECT `Pick #`, `CFL Team`, `Player`, `Position`, `College`
                FROM `table_1_10975034_4`
            ) t
        )
        WHERE rn = 1
    );
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, col4
    FROM (
        SELECT *,
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY col0) AS rn
        FROM (
            SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, col4
            FROM `table_1_10975034_4`
        ) t
    )
    WHERE rn IN (
        SELECT rn
        FROM (
            SELECT *,
                   ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY col1 ORDER BY col0)
            FROM (
                SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, col4
                FROM `table_1_10975034_4`
            ) t
        )
        WHERE rn = 1
    );
ans: [(27.0, 'hamilton tiger-cats', 'connor healey', 'db', 'wilfrid laurier')]

nl: What were the managerial changes and the dates of departure for each team?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Team` AS Team,
        `Manner of departure` AS Departure_Method,
        `Date of vacancy` AS Departure_Date,
        `Replaced by` AS New_Manager,
        `Date of appointment` AS Appointment_Date
    FROM (
        SELECT 
            `Team`, 
            `Manner of departure`, 
            `Date of vacancy`, 
            `Replaced by`, 
            `Date of appointment`,
            ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY `Team` ORDER BY `Date of vacancy`) AS rn
        FROM (
            SELECT 
                `Team`, 
                `Manner of departure`, 
                `Date of vacancy`, 
                `Replaced by`, 
                `Date of appointment`
            FROM `table_1_11207040_6`
        ) t
    )
    WHERE rn = 1;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0 AS Team,
        col2 AS Departure_Method,
        col3 AS Departure_Date,
        col4 AS New_Manager,
        col5 AS Appointment_Date
    FROM (

nl: What are the methods for each source along with their respective iOS percentages, sorted by source?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Source`, 
        GROUP_CONCAT(
            CONCAT(
                `Method`, 
                '- ', 
                `iOS`, 
                '%'
            ), 
            ', '
        ) AS `Methods and iOS`
    FROM 
        (
            SELECT 
                `Source`, 
                `Date`, 
                `Method`, 
                `iOS`, 
                ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY `Source` ORDER BY `Method`) AS rn
            FROM 
                table_1_11381701_3
            WHERE 
                `Date` >= 'May-13'
        )
    GROUP BY 
        `Source`
    ORDER BY 
        `Source`;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0, 
        GROUP_CONCAT(
            CONCAT(
                col2, 
                '- ', 
                col3, 
                '%'
            ), 
            ', '
        ) AS `Methods and iOS`
    FROM 
        (
            SELECT 
                col0, 
                col1, 
                col2, 
                col3, 
                ROW_NUMBER() OVER(PARTITION BY col0 ORDER BY col2) AS rn
            FROM 
                table_1_11381701_3
            WHERE 
                col1 >= 'May-13'
        )
    GROUP BY 
        col0
    ORDER BY 
        col0;

nl: For each country, what are the total number of participants, the highest number of male marathon finishers, the highest number of female marathon finishers, the highest number of male half marathon finishers, and the highest number of female half marathon finishers?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Country`, 
        SUM(`Total`) AS TotalParticipants,
        MAX(`Marathon (mens)`), 
        MAX(`Marathon (womens)`), 
        MAX(`Half Marathon (mens)`), 
        MAX(`Half Marathon (womens)`)
    FROM 
        `table_1_11391954_3`
    GROUP BY 
        `Country`
    ORDER BY 
        TotalParticipants DESC;
actual_sql:

        col0, 
        SUM(col1) AS TotalParticipants,
        MAX(col2), 
        MAX(col3), 
        MAX(col4), 
        MAX(col5)
    FROM 
        `table_1_11391954_3`
    GROUP BY 
        col0
    ORDER BY 
        TotalParticipants DESC;

nl: How many races were held on dates starting with March, May, or June 2nd, or August 5th?

    FROM (
        SELECT DISTINCT `Race Name`
        FROM `table_1_1140117_5`
        WHERE `Date` LIKE '1%March%' OR `Date` LIKE '2%May%' OR `Date` LIKE '2%June%' OR `Date` LIKE '5%August%'
    ) AS T1
    JOIN `table_1_1140117_5` AS T2 ON T1.`Race Name` = T2.`Race Name`
    GROUP BY T1.`Race Name`
    ORDER BY `Number of Races` DESC;

    FROM (

        FROM `table_1_1140117_5`
        WHERE col2 LIKE '1%March%' OR col2 LIKE '2%May%' OR col2 LIKE '2%June%' OR col2 LIKE '5%August%'
    ) AS T1
    JOIN `table_1_1140117_5` AS T2 ON T1.col0 = T2.col0
    GROUP BY T1.col0
    ORDER BY `Number of Races` DESC;

sql:

               WHEN `Engine code` LIKE '%T%' THEN 'Turbocharged'
               ELSE 'Non-Turbocharged'

    FROM `table_1_1147701_5`
    WHERE `Model name` LIKE '%D%'
    ORDER BY `Power (ps)` DESC;

    WHERE col0 LIKE '%D%'

nl: What is the maximum population in 1905, the average area of all gubernias, and how many gubernias have a name ending in "gubernia"?
sql:
SELECT 
    `Governorate` AS `Gubernia`, 
    MAX(`Population, in thousands,( 1905 )`) AS `Max Population 1905`, 
    AVG(CASE 
        WHEN `Name in Russian` LIKE '%губерния%' THEN `Area, in thousands of km 2`
        ELSE NULL 
    END) AS `Average Area for Gubernias`, 
    COUNT(CASE 
        WHEN `Name in Polish` LIKE '%gubernia%' THEN 1 
        ELSE NULL 
    END) AS `Count of Gubernias with Polish Name`
FROM 
    `table_1_11614581_3`
GROUP BY 
    `Governorate`;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
    col0 AS `Gubernia`, 
    MAX(col5) AS `Max Population 1905`, 
    AVG(CASE 
        WHEN col1 LIKE '%губерния%' THEN col4
        ELSE NULL 
    END) AS `Average Area for Gubernias`, 
    COUNT(CASE 
        WHEN col2 LIKE '%gubernia%' THEN 1 
        ELSE NULL 
    END) AS `Count of Gubernias with Polish Name`
FROM 
    `table_1_11614581_3`
GROUP BY 
    col0;

nl: Calculate the total weight, average weight, number of girls, and number of boys among the octuplets.
sql:
SELECT 
        SUM(`Weight at birth`) AS Total_Weight,
        AVG(`Weight at birth`) AS Average_Weight,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN `Gender` = 'Girl' THEN 1 END) AS NumberOf_Girls,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN `Gender` = 'Boy' THEN 1 END) AS NumberOf_Boys
    FROM 
        `table_1_11908801_1`;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        SUM(col3) AS Total_Weight,
        AVG(col3) AS Average_Weight,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN col2 = 'Girl' THEN 1 END) AS NumberOf_Girls,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN col2 = 'Boy' THEN 1 END) AS NumberOf_Boys
    FROM 
        `table_1_11908801_1`;

nl: How many matches did players born between January 1965 and January 1975 and also born between January 1975 and January 1985 play for Trinidad and Tobago?
sql:
SELECT T1.`Player`, COUNT(*) AS `Matches Played`
    FROM (
        SELECT `Player`, `Date of Birth`, `Batting Style`, `Bowling Style`, `First Class Team`
        FROM `table_1_11950720_8`
        WHERE `Date of Birth` >= '1 January 1965' AND `Date of Birth` < '1 January 1975'
    ) AS T1
    JOIN (
        SELECT `Player`, `Date of Birth`, `Batting Style`, `Bowling Style`, `First Class Team`
        FROM `table_1_11950720_8`
        WHERE `Date of Birth` >= '1 January 1975' AND `Date of Birth` < '1 January 1985'
    ) AS T2
    ON T1.`Player` = T2.`Player`
    WHERE T1.`First Class Team` = 'Trinidad and Tobago' AND T2.`First Class Team` = 'Trinidad and Tobago'
actual_sql:
SELECT T1.col1, COUNT(*) AS `Matches Played`
    FROM (
        SELECT col1, col2, col3, col4, col5
        FROM `table_1_11950720_8`
        WHERE col2 >= '1 January 1965' AND col2 < '1 January 1975'
    ) AS T1
    JOIN (
        SELECT col1, col2, col3, col4, col5
        FROM `table_1_11950720_8`
        WHERE col2 >= '1 January 1975' AND col2 < '1 January 1985'
    ) AS T2
    ON T1.col1 = T2.col1
    WHERE T1.col5 = 'Trinidad and Tobago' AND T2.col5 = 'Trinidad and Tobago'
ans: [(None, 0)]

sql:
SELECT 
    MAX(`Score`) AS `High Score`, 
    `Date`, 
    `Team` 
FROM 
    (SELECT 
         `Date`, 
         `Team`, 
         `Score`, 
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY `Team` ORDER BY `Score` DESC) AS rn 
     FROM 
         `table_1_11963536_11`)
WHERE rn = 1;
actual_sql:

    col2

         col1, 
         col2, 
         col3, 
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY col2 ORDER BY col3 DESC) AS rn 
     FROM 
         `table_1_11963536_11`)
WHERE rn = 1;

sql:
SELECT `Country`, 
       AVG(`Preliminaries`) AS Average_Preliminaries, 
       AVG(`Interview`) AS Average_Interview, 
       AVG(`Swimsuit`) AS Average_Swimsuit, 
       AVG(`Evening Gown`) AS Average_Evening_Gown, 
       AVG((`Preliminaries` + `Interview` + `Swimsuit` + `Evening Gown`) / 4) AS Overall_Average
FROM table_1_11970261_2
GROUP BY `Country`
ORDER BY Overall_Average DESC;
actual_sql:

       AVG(col1) AS Average_Preliminaries, 
       AVG(col2) AS Average_Interview, 
       AVG(col3) AS Average_Swimsuit, 
       AVG(col4) AS Average_Evening_Gown, 
       AVG((col1 + col2 + col3 + col4) / 4) AS Overall_Average
FROM table_1_11970261_2
GROUP BY col0
ORDER BY Overall_Average DESC;

nl: What are the total number of models supporting each version of NetFlow?
sql:
SELECT `Vendor and type`, 
       `Models`, 
       COUNT(`NetFlow Version`) AS `Total Models with Each Version`
FROM (
    SELECT `Vendor and type`, 
           `Models`, 
           `NetFlow Version`
    FROM `table_1_1206114_2`
    WHERE `NetFlow Version` IN ('v5', 'v8', 'v9')
)
GROUP BY `Vendor and type`, `Models`
ORDER BY `Vendor and type`, `Models`;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, 
       col1, 
       COUNT(col2) AS `Total Models with Each Version`
FROM (
    SELECT col0, 
           col1, 
           col2
    FROM `table_1_1206114_2`
    WHERE col2 IN ('v5', 'v8', 'v9')
)
GROUP BY col0, col1
ORDER BY col0, col1;

nl: What are the titles of the episodes with the latest original air date?
sql:
SELECT T1.`No. in season`, T1.`No. in series`, T1.`Title`, T1.`Directed by`, T1.`Written by`, T1.`Original air date`
    FROM `table_1_12226390_3` AS T1
    INNER JOIN (
        SELECT `No. in series`, MAX(`Original air date`) AS max_date
        FROM `table_1_12226390_3`
        GROUP BY `No. in series`
    ) AS T2
    ON T1.`No. in series` = T2.`No. in series` AND T1.`Original air date` = T2.max_date;

    FROM `table_1_12226390_3` AS T1
    INNER JOIN (
        SELECT col0, MAX(col5) AS max_date
        FROM `table_1_12226390_3`
        GROUP BY col0
    ) AS T2
    ON T1.col0 = T2.col0 AND T1.col5 = T2.max_date;

nl: What were the leaders in each classification for stages where any classification leader was in first place?
sql:
SELECT `Stage`, `Winner`, `General classification`, `Points classification`, 
           `Mountains classification`, `Young rider classification`, `Intergiro classification`
    FROM (
        SELECT `Stage`, `Winner`, `General classification`, `Points classification`, 
               `Mountains classification`, `Young rider classification`, `Intergiro classification`,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY `General classification`) AS general_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY `Points classification`) AS points_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY `Mountains classification`) AS mountains_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY `Young rider classification`) AS young_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY `Intergiro classification`) AS intergiro_rank
        FROM (
            SELECT `Stage`, `Winner`, `General classification`, `Points classification`, 
                   `Mountains classification`, `Young rider classification`, `Intergiro classification`
            FROM `table_1_12261714_2`
        )
    ) subquery
    WHERE general_rank = 1 OR points_rank = 1 OR mountains_rank = 1 OR young_rank = 1 OR intergiro_rank = 1;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, 
           col4, col5, col6
    FROM (
        SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, 
               col4, col5, col6,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY col2) AS general_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY col3) AS points_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY col4) AS mountains_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY col5) AS young_rank,
               RANK() OVER(ORDER BY col6) AS intergiro_rank
        FROM (
            SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, 
                   col4, col5, col6
            FROM `table_1_12261714_2`
        )
    ) subquery
    WHERE general_rank = 1 OR points_rank = 1 OR mountains_rank = 1 OR young_rank = 1 OR intergiro_rank = 1;

nl:
```What is the average number of conditions where each laboratory test result is prolonged for patients with acute liver failure?```
    ```What is the average number of conditions where each laboratory test (prothrombin time, partial thromboplastin time, bleeding time, and platelet count) is prolonged for patients with acute liver failure?```
sql:
SELECT `Condition`, AVG(CASE WHEN `Prothrombin time` = 'Prolonged' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Prolonged_PT, 
           AVG(CASE WHEN `Partial thromboplastin time` = 'Prolonged' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Prolonged_PTT, 
           AVG(CASE WHEN `Bleeding time` = 'Prolonged' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Prolonged_BT, 
           AVG(CASE WHEN `Platelet count` = 'Decreased' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Decreased_Platelets 
    FROM `table_1_1226250_1` 
    GROUP BY `Condition`;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, AVG(CASE WHEN col1 = 'Prolonged' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Prolonged_PT, 
           AVG(CASE WHEN col2 = 'Prolonged' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Prolonged_PTT, 
           AVG(CASE WHEN col3 = 'Prolonged' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Prolonged_BT, 
           AVG(CASE WHEN col4 = 'Decreased' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Decreased_Platelets 
    FROM `table_1_1226250_1` 
    GROUP BY col0;

nl: What are the total prominences of peaks whose prominence is greater than 1.5 times the average prominence?
sql:
SELECT `Peak`, SUM(`Prominence (m)`) AS TotalProminence
FROM table_1_12280396_1
WHERE `Prominence (m)` > (
    SELECT AVG(`Prominence (m)`) * 1.5
    FROM table_1_12280396_1
)
GROUP BY `Peak`;
actual_sql:
SELECT col1, SUM(col3) AS TotalProminence
FROM table_1_12280396_1
WHERE col3 > (
    SELECT AVG(col3) * 1.5
    FROM table_1_12280396_1
)

    ORDER BY `Residents per officer` DESC;

SELECT 
        `Municipality`, 
        `Population`, 
        `Area km²`, 
        `Density Population per km²`, 
        `Area`, 
        `County`, 
        CASE 
            WHEN `County` = 'Oslo' THEN 'Greater Oslo'
            ELSE `County`
        END AS `Region`
    FROM 
        `table_1_1246665_1`
    WHERE 
        `Density Population per km²` > 1000 OR `Population` > 100000;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0, 
        col1, 
        col2, 
        col3, 
        col4, 
        col5, 
        CASE 
            WHEN col5 = 'Oslo' THEN 'Greater Oslo'
            ELSE col5
        END AS `Region`
    FROM 
        `table_1_1246665_1`
    WHERE 
        col3 > 1000 OR col1 > 100000;

nl: : What are the top three clubs based on their goals for average?
sql:
SELECT `Club`, `Overall Record`, `Goals For`, `Goals For Avg.`, `Goals Against`, `Goals Against Avg.` 
    FROM (
        SELECT `Club`, `Overall Record`, `Goals For`, `Goals For Avg.`, `Goals Against`, `Goals Against Avg.`, 
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER(ORDER BY `Goals For Avg.` DESC) AS Rank_GoalsForAvg
        FROM table_1_1253396_5
    ) AS Subquery
    WHERE Rank_GoalsForAvg <= 3;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, col4, col5 
    FROM (
        SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, col4, col5, 
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER(ORDER BY col3 DESC) AS Rank_GoalsForAvg
        FROM table_1_1253396_5
    ) AS Subquery
    WHERE Rank_GoalsForAvg <= 3;

nl: Which club has the highest average points difference from their points scored and conceded?
sql:
SELECT `Club`, SUM(`Points for`) AS TotalPointsFor, SUM(`Points against`) AS TotalPointsAgainst, AVG(`Points for` - `Points against`) AS AveragePointsDifference 
FROM `table_1_12792876_2` 
GROUP BY `Club` 
ORDER BY `AveragePointsDifference` DESC 
LIMIT 1;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, SUM(col5) AS TotalPointsFor, SUM(col6) AS TotalPointsAgainst, AVG(col5 - col6) AS AveragePointsDifference 
FROM `table_1_12792876_2` 
GROUP BY col0 
ORDER BY `AveragePointsDifference` DESC 
LIMIT 1;

nl: What are the average total viewers, earliest broadcast date, latest broadcast date, and number of episodes for each series?

    `Series number`, 
    AVG(`Total viewers`) AS `Average viewers per episode`, 
    MIN(`Date of first broadcast`) AS `Earliest broadcast date`, 
    MAX(`Date of first broadcast`) AS `Latest broadcast date`,

nl: What is the winner and runner-up team for each year based on their ranking?
sql:
SELECT `Year`, 
           MAX(CASE WHEN `Rank` = 1 THEN `Team Name` END) AS `Winner`,
           MAX(CASE WHEN `Rank` = 2 THEN `Team Name` END) AS `Runner-Up`
    FROM (
        SELECT `Year`, 
               `Rank`, 
               `Team Name`, 
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY `Year` ORDER BY `Rank`) AS `Ranking`
        FROM (
            SELECT `Year`, 
                   `Connecticut`, 
                   `Maine`, 
                   `Massachusetts`, 
                   `New Hampshire`, 
                   `Rhode Island`, 
                   `Vermont` AS `Team Name`, 
                   RANK() OVER (ORDER BY `Connecticut` DESC, `Maine` DESC, `Massachusetts` DESC, `New Hampshire` DESC, `Rhode Island` DESC, `Vermont` DESC) AS `Rank`
            FROM table_1_13011547_1
        ) t
    ) t2
    WHERE `Ranking` = 1
    GROUP BY `Year`;

    FROM table_1_1322914_1
    GROUP BY `Release`, `Title`
    ORDER BY `Release`;

    FROM table_1_1322914_1
    GROUP BY col0, col1
    ORDER BY col0;

        WHEN `Result` LIKE '%death%' THEN 
            CONCAT(`Incumbent`,' died and ', `Incumbent` IN ('Lane Evans', 'Phil Crane'))
        ELSE NULL
    END AS `New Incumbent`, 
    `Candidates`
FROM 
    `table_1_1341586_14`

        ELSE NULL

    col5

    `table_1_1341586_14`

    `District`, 
    `Incumbent` AS `Incumbent Name`, 
    `Party`, 
    `First elected`, 
    CASE 
        WHEN `Result` LIKE '%Re-elected%' THEN 'Re-elected'
        WHEN `Result` LIKE '%Unopposed%' THEN 'Unopposed'
        ELSE 'Elected'
    END AS `Outcome`,
    CASE 
        WHEN `Result` LIKE '%gain%' THEN 'Gained'
    END
FROM 
    `table_1_1341738_34`;

    CASE 
        WHEN col4 LIKE '%gain%' THEN 'Gained'
    END
FROM 
    `table_1_1341738_34`;

nl: : How many seats were re-elected and how many were not?
sql:
SELECT 
        COUNT(`District`) AS Total_Seats_Changed,
        SUM(CASE 
                WHEN `Result` = 'Re-elected' THEN 1
                ELSE 0
            END) AS Seats_Re_Elected,
        SUM(CASE 
                WHEN `Result`!= 'Re-elected' THEN 1
                ELSE 0
            END) AS Seats_Not_Re_Elected
    FROM `table_1_1341843_15`;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        COUNT(col0) AS Total_Seats_Changed,
        SUM(CASE 
                WHEN col4 = 'Re-elected' THEN 1
                ELSE 0
            END) AS Seats_Re_Elected,
        SUM(CASE 
                WHEN col4!= 'Re-elected' THEN 1
                ELSE 0
            END) AS Seats_Not_Re_Elected
    FROM `table_1_1341843_15`;

    END AS `Outcome`
    FROM `table_1_1341843_44`
    WHERE `Result` NOT LIKE '%Lost%' AND `Result` NOT LIKE '%Unopposed%'
    ORDER BY `First elected` DESC;

    ORDER BY col3 DESC;

nl: How many districts saw incumbents re-elected in the 1934 United States House of Representatives elections?
sql:
SELECT `District`, `Incumbent`, `Party`, `First elected`, `Result`, 
           CASE 
               WHEN `Result` LIKE '%re-elected%' THEN 'Elected'
               ELSE 'Not Elected'
           END AS Election_Status,
           COUNT(*) AS Number_Elected
    FROM (
        SELECT `District`, `Incumbent`, `Party`, `First elected`, `Result`
        FROM `table_1_1342331_6`
        WHERE `Result` LIKE '%re-elected%'
            OR `Result` LIKE '%retired%'
            OR `Result` LIKE '%gained%'
    ) AS Elected_Results
    GROUP BY `District`, `Incumbent`, `Party`, `First elected`, `Result`
    ORDER BY `Number_Elected` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, col4, 
           CASE 
               WHEN col4 LIKE '%re-elected%' THEN 'Elected'
               ELSE 'Not Elected'
           END AS Election_Status,
           COUNT(*) AS Number_Elected
    FROM (
        SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, col4
        FROM `table_1_1342331_6`
        WHERE col4 LIKE '%re-elected%'
            OR col4 LIKE '%retired%'
            OR col4 LIKE '%gained%'
    ) AS Elected_Results
    GROUP BY col0, col1, col2, col3, col4
    ORDER BY `Number_Elected` DESC;

nl: : How many years
sql:
SELECT `District`, `Incumbent`, `Party`, `First elected`, 
           CASE 
               WHEN `Result` LIKE '%Re-elected%' THEN 'Re-election'
               ELSE 'Retirement'
           END AS Election_Type,
           MAX(`First elected`) OVER (PARTITION BY `District`) - `First elected` AS Duration_Since_First_Election
    FROM `table_1_1342359_15`
    WHERE `Result` LIKE '%Re-elected%' OR `Result` LIKE '%Retired%'
    GROUP BY `District`, `Incumbent`, `Party`, `First elected`, `Result`
    ORDER BY `Duration_Since_First_Election` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, col1, col2, col3, 
           CASE 
               WHEN col4 LIKE '%Re-elected%' THEN 'Re-election'
               ELSE 'Retirement'
           END AS Election_Type,
           MAX(col3) OVER (PARTITION BY col0) - col3 AS Duration_Since_First_Election
    FROM `table_1_1342359_15`
    WHERE col4 LIKE '%Re-elected%' OR col4 LIKE '%Retired%'
    GROUP BY col0, col1, col2, col3, col4
    ORDER BY `Duration_Since_First_Election` DESC;

nl: Which primary affiliations have the most stations with the earliest ownership dates?
sql:
SELECT T1.`City of license /Market`, T1.`Primary affiliation`, COUNT(*) AS StationCount
FROM `table_1_1353096_1` AS T1
JOIN (
    SELECT `Primary affiliation`, MIN(`Owned since`) AS MinOwnedSince
    FROM `table_1_1353096_1`
    GROUP BY `Primary affiliation`
) AS T2
ON T1.`Primary affiliation` = T2.`Primary affiliation` AND T1.`Owned since` = T2.MinOwnedSince
GROUP BY T1.`Primary affiliation`
ORDER BY T1.`Primary affiliation`;
actual_sql:
SELECT T1.col0, T1.col4, COUNT(*) AS StationCount
FROM `table_1_1353096_1` AS T1
JOIN (
    SELECT col4, MIN(col3) AS MinOwnedSince
    FROM `table_1_1353096_1`
    GROUP BY col4
) AS T2
ON T1.col4 = T2.col4 AND T1.col3 = T2.MinOwnedSince
GROUP BY T1.col4
ORDER BY T1.col4;

nl: Which programmes returned first after 1999, had the earliest return date after 2000, and the latest return date after 2005?
sql:

        `Programme`, 
        MAX(CASE WHEN `Date(s) of original removal` LIKE '%1999%' THEN `Date(s) of return` END) AS `FirstReturnAfter1999`,
        MIN(CASE WHEN `Date(s) of original removal` LIKE '%2000%' THEN `Date(s) of return` END) AS `EarliestReturnAfter2000`,
        MAX(CASE WHEN `Date(s) of original removal` LIKE '%2005%' THEN `Date(s) of return` END) AS `LatestReturnAfter2005`
    FROM 
        `table_1_13549921_18`
    GROUP BY 
        `Programme`;
actual_sql:

        col0,

nl:
```What season had the highest percentage of front row starts?```

    Explanation:
    - The query is looking for the season with the highest percentage of times a driver started on the front row.
    - It finds this by first determining the season with the highest overall percentage of front row starts.
    - Then, it identifies the driver who achieved the maximum front row starts in that season.
    - The question focuses on the season with the highest percentage, which directly addresses the purpose of the provided query without including unnecessary details. ```What season had the highest percentage of front row starts?```
sql:
SELECT `Season`, `Driver`, (`Front row starts` * 100 / `Entries`) AS `Percentage`
    FROM `table_1_13599687_37`
    WHERE `Front row starts` = (
        SELECT MAX(`Front row starts`)
        FROM `table_1_13599687_37`
        WHERE `Season` = (
            SELECT `Season`
            FROM `table_1_13599687_37`
            ORDER BY `Percentage` DESC
            LIMIT 1
        )
    );
actual_sql:
SELECT col2, col1, (col4 * 100 / col3) AS col5
    FROM `table_1_13599687_37`
    WHERE col4 = (
        SELECT MAX(col4)
        FROM `table_1_13599687_37`
        WHERE col2 = (
            SELECT col2
            FROM `table_1_13599687_37`
            ORDER BY col5 DESC
            LIMIT 1
        )
    );

nl: What are the regions, total populations, number of Catholics, their percentage of the total population, and their percentage of global Catholic population, sorted by the latter in descending order?
sql:
SELECT `Region`, `Total Population`, `Catholic`, 
           (`Catholic` * 100 / `Total Population`) AS `Percentage of Total Population`, 
           (`Catholic` * 100 / (SELECT SUM(`Catholic`) FROM `table_1_1364343_2`)) AS `Percentage of Global Catholic Pop.` 
    FROM `table_1_1364343_2`
    ORDER BY `Percentage of Global Catholic Pop.` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT col0, col1, col2, 
           (col2 * 100 / col1) AS `Percentage of Total Population`, 
           (col2 * 100 / (SELECT SUM(col2) FROM `table_1_1364343_2`)) AS `Percentage of Global Catholic Pop.` 
    FROM `table_1_1364343_2`
    ORDER BY `Percentage of Global Catholic Pop.` DESC;

nl: What are the top-ranked airports and their percentage change in total passengers from 2008 to 2009?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Rank`, 
        `Airport`, 
        (`Total Passengers 2009` - `Total Passengers 2008`) * 100 / `Total Passengers 2008` AS `Change Percentage 2008/09`
    FROM 
        `table_1_13836704_4`
    ORDER BY 
        `Change Percentage 2008/09` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0, 
        col1, 
        (col3 - col2) * 100 / col2 AS `Change Percentage 2008/09`
    FROM 
        `table_1_13836704_4`
    ORDER BY 
        `Change Percentage 2008/09` DESC;

nl: What are the top airport rankings along with their maximum total passengers, average percentage change from 2006/2007, total international passengers, total domestic passengers, total transit passengers, total aircraft movements, and total freight (metric tonnes)?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Rank`, 
        `Airport`, 
        MAX(`Total Passengers`) AS `Max Passengers`, 
        AVG(`% Change 2006/2007`) AS `Avg % Change`, 
        SUM(`International Passengers`) AS `Total International Passengers`, 
        SUM(`Domestic Passengers`) AS `Total Domestic Passengers`, 
        SUM(`Transit Passengers`) AS `Total Transit Passengers`, 
        SUM(`Aircraft Movements`) AS `Total Aircraft Movements`, 
        SUM(`Freight (Metric Tonnes)`) AS `Total Freight (Metric Tonnes)`
    FROM 
        `table_1_13836704_8`
    GROUP BY 
        `Rank`, 
        `Airport`
    ORDER BY 
        `Max Passengers` DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0, 
        col1, 
        MAX(col2) AS `Max Passengers`, 
        AVG(col3) AS `Avg % Change`, 
        SUM(col4) AS `Total International Passengers`, 
        SUM(col5) AS `Total Domestic Passengers`, 
        SUM(col6) AS `Total Transit Passengers`, 
        SUM(col7) AS `Total Aircraft Movements`, 
        SUM(col8) AS `Total Freight (Metric Tonnes)`
    FROM 
        `table_1_13836704_8`
    GROUP BY 
        col0, 
        col1
    ORDER BY 
        `Max Passengers` DESC;

nl: What is the rank, airport, and its corresponding maximum number of passengers, average percentage change from 2005/2006, total international passengers, total domestic passengers, total transit passengers, total aircraft movements, and total freight (metric tonnes) for the busiest airports?

SELECT 
        `Rank`, 
        `Airport`, 
        MAX(`Total Passengers`) AS Max_Passengers, 
        AVG(`% Change 2005/2006`) AS Avg_Change, 
        SUM(`International Passengers`) AS Total_International, 
        SUM(`Domestic Passengers`) AS Total_Domestic, 
        SUM(`Transit Passengers`) AS Total_Transit, 
        SUM(`Aircraft Movements`) AS Total_Aircraft, 
        SUM(`Freight (Metric Tonnes)`) AS Total_Freight 
    FROM 
        `table_1_13836704_9` 
    GROUP BY 
        `Rank`, 
        `Airport` 
    ORDER BY 
        Max_Passengers DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0, 
        col1, 
        MAX(col2) AS Max_Passengers, 
        AVG(col3) AS Avg_Change, 
        SUM(col4) AS Total_International, 
        SUM(col5) AS Total_Domestic, 
        SUM(col6) AS Total_Transit, 
        SUM(col7) AS Total_Aircraft, 
        SUM(col8) AS Total_Freight 
    FROM 
        `table_1_13836704_9` 
    GROUP BY 
        col0, 
        col1 
    ORDER BY 
        Max_Passengers DESC;

    AND `Representative 1`!= `Representative 4`
    AND `Representative 1`!= `Representative 5`

WHERE T1.`Score` IS NOT NULL AND T2.`Score` IS NOT NULL;

nl: What is the total area, average population, and capital city for each county?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Code`, 
        `County`, 
        `Former Province`, 
        SUM(CAST(REPLACE(`Area (km 2 )`, ',', '') AS REAL)) AS TotalArea,
        AVG(`Population Census 2009`) AS AvgPopulation,
        MAX(`Capital`) AS CapitalCity
    FROM 
        `table_1_1404456_1`
    GROUP BY 
        `Code`
    ORDER BY 
        `TotalArea` DESC;
actual_sql:

        col0, 
        col1, 
        col2, 
        SUM(CAST(REPLACE(col3, ',', '') AS REAL)) AS TotalArea,
        AVG(col4) AS AvgPopulation,
        MAX(col5) AS CapitalCity
    FROM 
        `table_1_1404456_1`
    GROUP BY 
        col0
    ORDER BY 
        `TotalArea` DESC;

        `Character Name`,

nl: How many schools have at least one principal listed in their records?
sql:
SELECT 
        `Elementary Schools` AS School_Name,
        COUNT(`Principal (2013-2014)`), 
        SUM(CASE WHEN `Principal (2013-2014)` IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Principals_Count,
        AVG(LENGTH(`Principal (2013-2014)`)) AS Average_Principal_Length,
        MAX(LENGTH(`Principal (2013-2014)`)) AS Longest_Principal_Name,
        MIN(LENGTH(`Principal (2013-2014)`) + LENGTH(`Assistant Principal (2013-2014)`) - LENGTH(REPLACE(`Assistant Principal (2013-2014)`,'', '')) + 1) AS Combined_Principal_Appt_Length
    FROM 
        `table_1_14254419_3`
    GROUP BY 
        `Elementary Schools`;
actual_sql:
SELECT 
        col0 AS School_Name,
        COUNT(col3), 
        SUM(CASE WHEN col3 IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS Principals_Count,
        AVG(LENGTH(col3)) AS Average_Principal_Length,
        MAX(LENGTH(col3)) AS Longest_Principal_Name,
        MIN(LENGTH(col3) + LENGTH(col4) - LENGTH(REPLACE(col4,'', '')) + 1) AS Combined_Principal_Appt_Length
    FROM 
        `table_1_14254419_3`
    GROUP BY 
        col0;

nl: What are the shirt numbers, nationalities, player names, birth dates, heights, and positions for the players whose average height across all players is higher than their individual average height?
sql:
SELECT T1.`Shirt No`, T1.`Nationality`, T1.`Player`, T1.`Birth Date`, T1.`Height`, T1.`Position`
    FROM `table_1_14363116_1` AS T1
    INNER JOIN (
        SELECT `Shirt No`, AVG(`Height`) AS AvgHeight
        FROM `table_1_14363116_1`
        GROUP BY `Shirt No`
    ) AS T2 ON T1.`Shirt No` = T2.`Shirt No`
    WHERE T2.AvgHeight > (
        SELECT AVG(`Height`)
        FROM `table_1_14363116_1`
    )
    ORDER BY T2.AvgHeight DESC;
actual_sql:
SELECT T1.col0, T1.col1, T1.col2, T1.col3, T1.col4, T1.col5
    FROM `table_1_14363116_1` AS T1
    INNER JOIN (
        SELECT col0, AVG(col4) AS AvgHeight
        FROM `table_1_14363116_1`
        GROUP BY col0
    ) AS T2 ON T1.col0 = T2.col0
    WHERE T2.AvgHeight > (
        SELECT AVG(col4)
        FROM `table_1_14363116_1`
    )
    ORDER BY T2.AvgHeight DESC;
